programme.title: Rio Lobo (1970)
programme.desc: Former wartime enemies unite to track down the leader of a Texas outlaw gang who also sold Union secrets to the rebels during the Civil War.

programme.title: McLintock! (1963)
programme.desc: Story of an aging cattle baron and his divorce-minded wife, who walked out on him two years ago without a word of explanation and has been living back East and running in very fancy circles.

programme.title: North to Alaska (1960)
programme.desc: Prospecting partners in Alaska find gold, prompting one to ask the other if he will escort the man's fiance on a journey to join them.

programme.title: The Comancheros (1961)
programme.desc: A Texas Ranger runs across a gang of white renegades, called the Comancheros, who are trading guns and other contraband with marauding Comanches from a secret hideout in Mexico. He goes undercover as a partner with a vicious outlaw who is a contact man with the Comancheros and knows the whereabouts of their hideout in Mexico. Director Michael Curtiz's last film.

programme.title: The Undefeated (1969)
programme.desc: Feuding Union and Confederate Generals who battled each other during the Civil War clash again as they each lead a different group of people out west, but eventually work together when attacked by Mexicans.

programme.title: Guadalcanal Diary (1943)
programme.desc: One soldier chronicles his experiences at Guadalcanal, exploring the battles and lives of other soldiers as well as his own.

programme.title: Twelve O'Clock High (1949)
programme.desc: Best Picture nominee about an embattled Army Air Corps general who takes over the 918th Bomber Group for raids over World War II Germany when he deems their previous commander has gotten too close with his men.

programme.title: Gentleman's Agreement (1947)
programme.desc: The experiences of a journalist who pretends to be Jewish to gather data for an exposé on anti-Semitism, and the hatred he is subjected to that takes its toll on his personal life.

programme.title: Rough Magic (1995)
programme.desc: A 1950s reporter (Russell Crowe) is hired to find a magician's assistant (Bridget Fonda) who fled to Mexico after witnessing a murder involving her fiancé (D.W. Moffett). Ansell: Jim Broadbent. Magician: Kenneth Mars. Clare Peploe directed.

programme.title: Chances Are (1989)
programme.desc: A widow discovers her daughter's boyfriend is the reincarnation of her husband.

programme.title: Lucas (1986)
programme.desc: Teen charmer about friendships and first loves among a trio of high schoolers.

programme.title: Ice Castles (1978)
programme.desc: A champion skater's medal hopes are dashed when she is stricken blind, but a relationship with a caring young man helps her realize her dreams.

programme.title: Across the Tracks (1990)
programme.desc: Two brothers?one a delinquent, the other a perfectionist?are pitted against each other as track stars from rival high schools.

programme.title: Eat My Dust! (1976)
programme.desc: A sheriff's son appropriates a race car to impress his girlfriend.

programme.title: The Night Before (1988)
programme.desc: Farce about a nerd who takes a date to the prom and wakes up with amnesia.

programme.title: Imagine That (2009)
programme.desc: An ambitious financial whiz sacrifices time with his 7-year-old daughter for the sake of his job. One day his daughter's imaginary world unexpectedly helps his career, prompting him to improve their strained relationship.

programme.title: One-Eyed Jacks (1961)
programme.desc: A man seeks revenge against a former accomplice, now a respected sheriff, who betrayed him, leaving him to be captured and jailed.

programme.title: You Only Live Once (1937)
programme.desc: Based partially on the story of Bonnie and Clyde, Eddie Taylor is an ex-convict who cannot get a break after being released from prison. When he is framed for murder, Taylor is forced to flee with his wife Joan Graham and baby. While escaping prison after being sentenced to death, Taylor becomes a real murderer, condemning himself and Joan to a life of crime and death on the road.

programme.title: The Man Who Watched the Trains Go By (1953)
programme.desc: A business owner and his clerk go head to head over the company funds.

programme.title: Lightning Strikes Twice (1951)
programme.desc: A Texas rancher acquitted of his wife's murder by one juror's vote falls in love with an actress, and a complex web of jealousy and attraction ensues.

programme.title: Whiplash (1948)
programme.desc: An invalid, disabled in the ring, lives vicariously through his wife's paramour by training him to be a championship boxer.

programme.title: The Snake Pit (1948)
programme.desc: A seemingly normal married woman behaves so erratically that her husband asks that she get professional help, whereupon she is confined to a state hospital; she is well-treated by her kindly doctor, but abused by patients and matrons alike. A Best Picture nominee.

programme.title: I Was a Communist for the FBI (1951)
programme.desc: Story of Matt Cvetic (Frank Lovejoy), who joined the Reds to gather information for the FBI. Moves fast. Eve: Dorothy Hart. Mason: Philip Carey. Blandon: James Millican. Krowley: Richard Webb. Gerhardt Eisler: Konstantin Shayne.

programme.title: High Wall (1947)
programme.desc: A World War II veteran suffering from a recurring brain injury teams with a woman psychiatrist to prove himself innocent of his wife's murder.

programme.title: Backlash (1947)
programme.desc: A body found in the wreck of an automobile begins a tale of murder. Catherine: Jean Rogers. Richard: Richard Travis. McMullen: Larry Blake. Marian: Louise Currie. Morland: John Eldredge. The Stranger: Leonard Strong. O'Neil: Robert Shayne. Red: Douglas Fowley. Carey: Richard Benedict. Slow. Directed by Eugene Forde.
